article_title: Credit Suisse CEO: No 'Material Issues' Found During Forex Review
article_text:
ZURICH—Credit Suisse Group AG hasn't uncovered any serious problems during review of its foreign exchange business amid various regulatory probes into possible manipulation, the chief executive of Switzerland's second-biggest bank said Thursday.

"We are looking into our business," said Brady Dougan, CEO of Zurich-based Credit Suisse, during a media event. Mr. Dougan said the bank has "done a fair amount of work"...
